
In the Array Game assignment you have had to review and revisit concepts you may have forgotten about. These will all be tested on the final exam!
What is an array?
An int array is the number of positions on the "x-axis". If the number of pistions you wanted is 5 then it goes 01234 each one being a place the object could go.

How does one make a simple array of Strings?
String myString[];
myString = new String {"Hello"};

What is the syntax for a 2-D array?
A 2D array makes the x,y of a grid.
Syntax:
int [][] array = new int [5] [10];

What is the syntax for a 3-D array?
A 3D arrays makes a x, y, z. An array makes a lines. A 2D array makes a square. A 3D array makes a cude.
int [][] array = new int [5] [10] [15];

